text: 165 (one hundred sixty-five) is a whole number. It comes after 164 and before 166. == In mathematics == *165 is a composite number. Its factors include 3, 5, and 11. 165 = 3 × 5 × 11. *165 is also a binomial coefficient. It is the number of ways to choose 3 objects from 11 (written as “11 choose 3”). Category:Integers
title: 165 (number)
